# ScholarPass Project Overview

**AI-Powered Personalized Learning Platform** - Turborepo monorepo with TypeScript.

## Project Structure

```
apps/
  api/       # Express.js REST API (Node.js 20+)
  web/       # Next.js 14+ frontend (App Router)
packages/
  shared/    # Common types, utils, constants
```

## Key Conventions

- **Package manager**: npm workspaces
- **Build**: Turborepo (`turbo run dev/build/test`)
- **Formatting**: Prettier (no semicolons, single quotes, 2-space indent)
- **Commits**: Conventional commits (feat/fix/docs/refactor)
- **Node**: v20+ required

## API Response Format

Always use consistent response format:

```typescript
// Success
{ success: true, data: T, message?: string }

// Error
{ success: false, error: string, details?: ValidationError[] }

// Paginated
{ success: true, data: T[], pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages } }
```

## Import Aliases

- API: Relative imports (`../utils/`)
- Web: `@/` alias maps to `src/`
- Shared: `@scholarpass/shared`

## Environment

- API runs on port 3001
- Web runs on port 3000
- PostgreSQL + Redis required
